description._content: Catalog #: 09_00977 Title: Colonel Cleon Eugene Freeman Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Group of 10 men identified as 'Dwinell, Graham, Freeman, Billingsley, Bremen, Joe Cobbs, Keaple, Lauth, Cassidy, Mac' standing in front of a Curtiss Racer aircraft, Cleon Freeman was a Captain of the 110th Air Corps Observation Squadron during World War II and served as a liaison officer between the Ninth Air Force and ground forces working in England. He was awarded the Croix de Guerre in 1940 and the Bronze Star Medal in 1944, Corporation Name: Curtiss Aeroplane and Motor Company Tags: Colonel Cleon Eugene Freeman Special Collection Photo,Â 1928,Â Curtiss Aeroplane and Motor Company Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
